      "message": "Let\u0027s make some of these arguments optional:\n\nimport argparse\nif __name__ \u003d\u003d \u0027__main__\u0027:\n    parser \u003d argparse.ArgumentParser(description\u003d\u0027Generate args.gn file.\u0027)\n    parser.add_argument(\u0027target_build_dir\u0027)\n    parser.add_argument(\u0027android_ndk_dir\u0027 )\n    parser.add_argument(\u0027--arch\u0027,  metavar\u003d\u0027architecture\u0027, default\u003d\u0027arm\u0027,\n        help\u003d\u0027defaults to \"arm\", can be \"arm\" \"arm64\" \"x86\" or \"x64\"\u0027)\n    parser.add_argument(\u0027--api\u0027, type\u003dint, metavar\u003d\u0027api_version\u0027, default\u003d26, help\u003d\u0027defaults to 26\u0027)\n    parser.add_argument(\u0027--use_workarounds\u0027, default\u003dFalse, action\u003d\u0027store_true\u0027)\n    a \u003d parser.parse_args()\n    a.use_workarounds \u003d \u0027true\u0027 if a.use_workarounds else \u0027false\u0027 \n    make_args_gn(a.target_build_dir,\n                 a.android_ndk_dir,\n                 a.arch,\n                 a.api,\n                 a.use_workarounds)\n\nAnd then update the README.",
